-- Russia Protests Libya Prison Sentences, Foreign Ministry Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-06-05T17:31:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/russia-protests-libya-prison-sentences-foreign-ministry-says.html
Russia handed a note of protest to
 Libya ’s charge d’affaires over a court-martial verdict brought
in June 4 in Tripoli against two Russian citizens, the Foreign
Affairs Ministry said in a  statement  on website today.  Russian citizens Alexander Shadrov and Vladimir Dolgov were
convicted by a Libyan court on June 4 of cooperating with the
Muammar Gaddafi regime, Interfax reported. Shadrov received a
life sentence, while Dolgov was given a 10-year prison term,
according to the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
